<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 11 at 4:41AM EST  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Moderate to Heavy Snowfall North of US-6...
Snow has begun moving into western areas and has reduced
visibility to 2 miles or less in Berrien county already. This is
expected to spread east during the morning hours and will
create slushy conditions on roadways.
Use caution while driving in areas with snow and allow extra time
to reach your destination.</description>
